activities.name: Review the Code
activities.description: Review the source code of the Software System.

activities.name: Refactor the Code
activities.description: Refactor the source code of Software System without behaviour changing.

alphas.name: Stakeholders
alphas.description: The people, groups, or organizations who affector are affected by a software system

alphas.name: Opportunity
alphas.description: The set of circumstances that makes it appropriate to develop or change a software system

alphas.name: Requirements
alphas.description: What the software system must do to address the opportunity and satisfy the stakeholders

alphas.name: Software System
alphas.description: A system made up of software, hardware, and data that provides its primary value by the execution ofthe software

alphas.name: Team
alphas.description: The group of people actively engaged in the development, maintenance, delivery or support of a specific software system

alphas.name: Way of Working
alphas.description: The tailored set of practices and tools used by the team membersto guide and support their work

alphas.name: Work
alphas.description: Activity involving mental or physical effort done in order to achieve a result

alphas.name: Antipattern
alphas.description: A common inefficient solution to a typical problem. It does not cause the application to work incorrectly, however, it may cause future modification and reuse problems.

checkpoints.name: Stakeholder groups identified
checkpoints.description: All the different groups of stakeholders that are, or will be, affected by the development and operation of the software system are identified

checkpoints.name: Key Stakeholder groups represented
checkpoints.description: There is agreement on the stakeholder groups to be represented. At a minimum, the stakeholders groups that fund, use, support, and maintain the system have been considered.

checkpoints.name: Responsibilities defined
